					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on the weekly sections Be-shalaḥ, Yitro and Mishpaṭim (Exodus 13:17-24:18).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Judeo-Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="270v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Shemot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש שמות </title>
							<note>
								<p>The unpointed Hebrew text of chapters 13:17-14:5, 14:29-15:19, 15:22-20:26, 21:12-24:18 is embodied. </p>
								<p>Each Hebrew verse is followed by an Arabic translation.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>The contents of this volume agree with the corresponding portions of Or 2545, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">311</ref>.</filiation>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269" xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Abu al-Faraj Furḳan, active 11th century <addName>Yeshuʻah ben Yehudah</addName>
								</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/58767269" xml:lang="he">ישועה בן יהודה</persName>
							</author>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">בשם י'י נע' ונצ' פראשה מקדמה לאמר לאסורים צאו וכו'.<locus n="2r"/>
							</incipit>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 13th to 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>270 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>212</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>85/90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>270 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 32 quires of 10 leaves each, with exception of 8th and 9th which have 11 and 8 leaves respectively).</p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters on the left-hand upper corner of the first page of a quire are found on folios 63r, 74r, 82r, 92r, 102r, 112r, 122r, 142r, 152r.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Lacunae after folios 3 and 6, and quires 17-20 are entirely lost.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="19" writtenLines="19">
									<p>The unpointed Hebrew text is embodied.</p>
									<p>Has many marginal notes.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
